1
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:37,799
Please.

2
00:00:39,759 --> 00:00:40,799
Uncle Min.

3
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:43,759
Among my father's belongings,

4
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:47,159
I found an ancient scroll about Mengna Valley.

5
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:48,479
It says

6
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:51,399
the map of the heart of Mengna Valley

7
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:56,159
is hidden in the Silver Eye at Juedabu City Ruins.

8
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,399
What Silver Eye?

9
00:01:00,439 --> 00:01:01,399
To an outsider,

10
00:01:01,679 --> 00:01:04,120
the Silver Eye looks like a giant relief.

11
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:06,640
But to those in the know,

12
00:01:06,879 --> 00:01:07,640
what is it?

13
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:10,079
It's a coordinate map!

14
00:01:11,599 --> 00:01:13,280
This ancient scroll states

15
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:14,599
that at its center is drawn

16
00:01:14,599 --> 00:01:16,959
a territorial map of Mengna Valley.

17
00:01:17,319 --> 00:01:18,799
By following this map,

18
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,480
the location of Mengna Valley

19
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:22,719
can definitely be found within the Silver Eye.

20
00:01:24,439 --> 00:01:25,400
So you mean

21
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,280
we first need to go to Juedabu City Ruins

22
00:01:27,319 --> 00:01:28,319
and find the Silver Eye.

23
00:01:28,359 --> 00:01:29,159
Exactly!

24
00:01:30,599 --> 00:01:32,079
Then we should get He Shutong.

25
00:01:33,719 --> 00:01:35,799
Brother Chen really gets me!

26
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:37,719
I won't lie to you,

27
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:41,599
I've thoroughly studied every paper

28
00:01:41,719 --> 00:01:43,719
Miss He wrote about Mengna Valley.

29
00:01:44,439 --> 00:01:45,640
So Miss He

30
00:01:45,719 --> 00:01:47,760
is an indispensable member

31
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,840
of this trip to Mengna Valley.

32
00:01:50,159 --> 00:01:50,879
Brother Chen,

33
00:01:52,359 --> 00:01:54,879
I can only turn to you for this.

34
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:57,359
Please help me persuade Miss He.

35
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,080
Put down those walnuts.

36
00:02:09,599 --> 00:02:10,960
Stop fiddling with them.

37
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:13,439
This is a fantastic opportunity.

38
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,080
Here's the deal, Old Lu.

39
00:02:15,159 --> 00:02:16,719
Come back with me now to draw up the contract.

40
00:02:16,919 --> 00:02:17,759
Four people.

41
00:02:18,199 --> 00:02:19,879
Two thousand per person, per day.

42
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,919
That's not bad.

43
00:02:21,919 --> 00:02:23,520
Nobody turns down money.

44
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:24,439
But still,

45
00:02:24,479 --> 00:02:26,319
won't this go against our principles?

46
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,879
We have to notify the organization.

47
00:02:28,879 --> 00:02:30,800
At the very least, Curator Zhu needs to know.

48
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:32,319
Fine, fine, here's what we do.

49
00:02:32,439 --> 00:02:34,159
We'll draw up the contract, no delay.

50
00:02:34,319 --> 00:02:36,159
Let Old Chen report to the organization and Curator Zhu.

51
00:02:36,159 --> 00:02:37,080
Just give them a heads-up.

52
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:38,199
And give him a day off while he's at it.

53
00:02:38,199 --> 00:02:39,879
Let him win over Advisor He.

54
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,759
First thing tomorrow, I'll go get my visa.

55
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:43,800
If nothing unexpected comes up,

56
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,000
I'm going abroad next week.

57
00:02:47,719 --> 00:02:49,159
When did you decide this?

58
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,000
Just now.

59
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,479
Okay, okay, okay.

60
00:02:57,479 --> 00:02:58,520
Let me tell you, I...

61
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,599
I could slap myself right now.

62
00:03:00,599 --> 00:03:01,319
You know that?

63
00:03:01,319 --> 00:03:02,560
I really regret it.

64
00:03:02,759 --> 00:03:03,360
I shouldn't have

65
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,000
urged you and Advisor He to go together.

66
00:03:05,039 --> 00:03:07,000
At least I'm going abroad for treatment.

67
00:03:07,039 --> 00:03:07,719
Brother,

68
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,879
can your illness even be cured abroad?

69
00:03:09,879 --> 00:03:11,360
Don't you know that deep down?

70
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,280
I know what Advisor He is thinking.

71
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,400
She's a woman in a tough spot, so she's emotional.

72
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:17,199
How did you get brainwashed too?

73
00:03:17,639 --> 00:03:19,000
Why do you keep pushing me to go to Mengna Valley?

74
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,199
What's your angle?

75
00:03:20,319 --> 00:03:21,159
My life is on the line.

76
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:22,919
You think I care about his lousy money?

77
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:23,719
Brother,

78
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,159
I went to all that trouble setting this up.

79
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,520
Do you think it was for the money?

80
00:03:29,639 --> 00:03:31,039
That's a question I should be asking you.

81
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:33,680
Stop, stop.

82
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:39,120
Why am I telling you to go to Mengna Valley?

83
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,199
Because I know

84
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:41,599
Uncle Min has the same illness as you.

85
00:03:41,599 --> 00:03:42,639
He's going to Mengna Valley

86
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:44,120
to save his own life.

87
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:46,719
You actually have the nerve to make up this nonsense?

88
00:03:47,319 --> 00:03:49,599
Fatty, you can't joke about stuff like this.

89
00:03:49,599 --> 00:03:50,400
Get lost.

90
00:03:50,639 --> 00:03:51,639
Who's joking?

91
00:03:52,039 --> 00:03:53,400
How many years have you known me?

92
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,759
Am I the kind of guy who'd joke

93
00:03:54,759 --> 00:03:55,960
about a brother's life?

94
00:04:01,639 --> 00:04:04,280
Boss, with your current condition,

95
00:04:04,719 --> 00:04:06,439
I think this trip to Mengna Valley,

96
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:08,240
let me go in your place.

97
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:10,240
No way you can take my place.

98
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,639
Where this illness really comes from,

99
00:04:14,479 --> 00:04:15,560
and whether it can be cured,

100
00:04:16,319 --> 00:04:18,680
that's something I need to go and find out myself.

101
00:04:22,839 --> 00:04:24,279
This is seriously bizarre.

102
00:04:25,199 --> 00:04:26,040
Uncle Min,

103
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:28,720
how does he have this same scar too?

104
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,519
Commander Chen,

105
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,519
I promised to help you break the curse on you,

106
00:04:33,759 --> 00:04:35,480
and I never thought of quitting halfway.

107
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:37,879
But Commander Chen,

108
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:39,600
if you die in some hospital abroad

109
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:41,079
without ever knowing why,

110
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,160
I, Fatty,

111
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,240
will never forgive you, not in this lifetime.

112
00:04:50,079 --> 00:04:51,519
Look at the mess we're in.

113
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:02,879
Visa denied.

114
00:05:03,839 --> 00:05:05,240
Didn't I tell you to memorize the script?

115
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,040
I did memorize it.

116
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,319
I answered exactly as written.

117
00:05:07,319 --> 00:05:09,120
You never wanted to go abroad, did you?

118
00:05:09,639 --> 00:05:10,800
Just because the visa got denied,

119
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,399
you can't dismiss what I planned.

120
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,240
Then what about those adventure books by your bed?

121
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,160
How do you explain that?

122
00:05:15,319 --> 00:05:17,279
If you didn't want to go abroad, you could've just told me.

123
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,319
If you want to go exploring, I'll come with you.

124
00:05:19,759 --> 00:05:20,439
I just want to ask you,

125
00:05:20,439 --> 00:05:21,639
before you make every decision,

126
00:05:21,639 --> 00:05:23,079
did you ever think to discuss it with me?

127
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:24,240
Or at least let me know?

128
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,279
Shutong.

129
00:05:25,439 --> 00:05:27,079
Shutong, let me explain.

130
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:29,839
I memorized the script word for word.

131
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:31,560
I answered seriously, I swear.

132
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,079
Shutong.

133
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:35,199
Good morning, sir.

134
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:36,959
What do you do for a living?

135
00:05:38,399 --> 00:05:39,759
I work at a museum.

136
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,560
I'm an archaeologist.

137
00:05:42,879 --> 00:05:46,040
What's your current salary?

138
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,279
One thousand a month.

139
00:05:49,439 --> 00:05:50,839
Why are you going abroad?

140
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,319
Because I'm ill.

141
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:57,560
I need to try a new treatment.

142
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,399
How about

143
00:06:12,199 --> 00:06:13,639
we consider a fake marriage?

144
00:06:14,439 --> 00:06:15,720
Who'd ever fake-marry you?

145
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,040
Oh, right.

146
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,480
There's something important

147
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,279
I need to discuss with you.

148
00:06:22,279 --> 00:06:23,240
It's about the Lingxiao Pearl.

149
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:23,959
Get lost.

150
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,279
Bodhisattva, please bless us.

151
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,439
Keep us guys safe and sound,

152
00:06:32,439 --> 00:06:33,399
in harmony together,

153
00:06:33,519 --> 00:06:35,600
and please don't let us fall apart.

154
00:06:35,759 --> 00:06:37,439
Bless us, bless us, bless us.

155
00:06:41,879 --> 00:06:42,319
Coming!

156
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,040
Where's Fatty?

157
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,959
Well, I called him.

158
00:06:47,279 --> 00:06:48,759
Whether he shows up, who knows.

159
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:50,040
Fine, forget him then.

160
00:06:51,879 --> 00:06:52,839
What's up?

161
00:06:52,839 --> 00:06:54,160
I've worked things out with Uncle Min.

162
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,480
He's already in Chengdu.

163
00:06:55,879 --> 00:06:57,240
We leave first thing tomorrow morning.

164
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,720
After we meet up, we head straight west.

165
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:04,560
That's what brothers are for.

166
00:07:05,399 --> 00:07:06,879
What do you mean, "forget him"?

167
00:07:08,839 --> 00:07:10,199
The ancestors' rule:

168
00:07:10,439 --> 00:07:12,240
United we live, divided we die.

169
00:07:12,879 --> 00:07:14,920
That rule can't be broken, you know that?

170
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,000
I won't waste any more words.

171
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:18,759
This time,

172
00:07:19,399 --> 00:07:20,839
unlike any tomb expedition we've done before,

173
00:07:20,839 --> 00:07:21,720
is completely different.

174
00:07:22,199 --> 00:07:23,639
We're heading to the west.

175
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:27,519
The climate, altitude, terrain,

176
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:29,079
any single one of these factors

177
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,920
could get us killed.

178
00:07:31,759 --> 00:07:33,240
None of us can let our guard down.

179
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,519
That's point one.

180
00:07:36,199 --> 00:07:37,000
Point two,

181
00:07:38,079 --> 00:07:39,680
and the most important one in my view,

182
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:44,160
I, Chen Youxi, may very well die out there.

183
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:48,519
Anytime, anywhere,

184
00:07:50,879 --> 00:07:52,199
if I tell you to leave,

185
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,879
you must listen to me.

186
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,680
No hesitation whatsoever.

187
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,720
Rule two: you don't get the final say.

188
00:08:22,199 --> 00:08:22,959
Brother Chen!

189
00:08:22,959 --> 00:08:24,839
I've been waiting for you guys forever.

190
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:29,160
Hello.

191
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,560
Hello, hello, hello.

192
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,920
And this must be

193
00:08:31,959 --> 00:08:33,440
Miss He Shutong, am I right?

194
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,200
Yes.

195
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:36,600
I've read many of your papers.

196
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,039
A true honor to read them.

197
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:40,519
Meeting you today, you're as elegant as your writing.

198
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,679
A pleasure, truly.

199
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:42,759
You flatter me, I don't deserve it.

200
00:08:42,759 --> 00:08:43,600
Come, come, come.

201
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,639
Please, come on in.

202
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,360
Come, come.

203
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:48,840
Take a seat anywhere.

204
00:08:49,399 --> 00:08:50,639
Bi Huaqiang,

205
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:51,960
get everyone seated.

206
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,559
I'll go fetch some fine tea for you all.

207
00:08:53,559 --> 00:08:54,279
Great, great, great.

208
00:09:26,879 --> 00:09:27,679
Fatty,

209
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,440
Come here, come here, come here.

210
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,039
Look at this.

211
00:09:33,799 --> 00:09:34,440
Pretty cool, huh?

212
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,080
Cock it.

213
00:09:44,519 --> 00:09:45,279
What are you doing?

214
00:09:46,039 --> 00:09:46,879
Don't touch it.

215
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,879
You could've just said so.

216
00:09:49,879 --> 00:09:51,840
Who are you trying to scare with that crappy slingshot?

217
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:53,159
It's a crossbow.

218
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,279
Range of 100 meters.

219
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:56,720
Within 50 meters,

220
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,600
It's like a Type 54 pistol.

221
00:09:58,639 --> 00:09:59,440
A pistol?

222
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:01,440
Look how cocky you are.

223
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:03,120
What gun hasn't Fatty seen?

224
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,840
Come on, shoot here.

225
00:10:08,919 --> 00:10:09,639
Stop it!

226
00:10:09,639 --> 00:10:10,320
Don't move.

227
00:10:15,639 --> 00:10:16,960
What's going on? What's wrong?

228
00:10:17,159 --> 00:10:19,200
What's happening here?

229
00:10:21,399 --> 00:10:23,200
These are my guests.

230
00:10:23,559 --> 00:10:24,679
What are you doing? Let go!

231
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:25,320
Drop it.

232
00:10:28,679 --> 00:10:29,360
You.

233
00:10:30,679 --> 00:10:31,840
These are all guests I invited.

234
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,279
Is this how you treat my guests?

235
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,120
Apologize.

236
00:10:35,799 --> 00:10:36,200
My apologies.

237
00:10:36,279 --> 00:10:36,960
Bi Huaqiang.

238
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,159
Let me tell you,

239
00:10:39,799 --> 00:10:41,240
If it weren't out of respect for Uncle Min,

240
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,519
I'd teach you a lesson.

241
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,000
Alright, alright, alright.

242
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,399
Fatty, Fatty, please have a seat.

243
00:10:45,399 --> 00:10:46,240
Don't be angry.

244
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:47,559
Brother Chen, I'm so sorry.

245
00:10:47,559 --> 00:10:48,720
Come, take the seat of honor.

246
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,159
Come on, sit at the head.

247
00:10:55,399 --> 00:10:55,879
Let's go.

248
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:04,679
Brother Chen, please sit down.

249
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:07,200
Ah Zhong is young and doesn't know better.

250
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,759
But let me tell you something,

251
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,120
His wilderness survival skills

252
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,799
Are truly extraordinary.

253
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,840
And this crossbow,

254
00:11:13,919 --> 00:11:15,039
Don't underestimate it either.

255
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,000
He made it himself.

256
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,159
Now you've met,

257
00:11:18,159 --> 00:11:20,039
Let me give you a proper introduction.

258
00:11:20,039 --> 00:11:23,960
She's the head coach of the Krav Maga Association.

259
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:27,919
Thank you.

260
00:11:30,919 --> 00:11:31,759
Teacher Lu,

261
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:33,759
We met on the train.

262
00:11:33,759 --> 00:11:34,600
Teacher Li,

263
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,600
I caused trouble at your lecture.

264
00:11:37,919 --> 00:11:39,879
Teacher Chen, we meet again.

265
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,879
I remember now, Fatty,

266
00:11:46,159 --> 00:11:48,559
she's the girl you were hitting on, on the train!

267
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,120
I remember, I remember.

268
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,320
We meet again here.

269
00:11:52,399 --> 00:11:53,960
You know Uncle Min too?

270
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,799
I'm Uncle Min's goddaughter.

271
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:56,879
My name is An Xiang.

272
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,519
I've long heard about your archaeology exploits.

273
00:11:59,679 --> 00:12:01,080
You're all my idols.

274
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:01,960
Of course I had to come.

275
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:04,399
But with you wearing those sunglasses, beautiful,

276
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,639
I failed to recognize you.

277
00:12:07,799 --> 00:12:08,600
An Xiang.

278
00:12:09,639 --> 00:12:10,960
Take off the sunglasses.

279
00:12:15,039 --> 00:12:15,840
Turn around.

280
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:43,200
An Xiang's eyes,

281
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,360
they're no ordinary eyes.

282
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:47,759
Any unclean things,

283
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,159
she can sense them all.

284
00:12:50,879 --> 00:12:53,840
An Xiang, Ah Zhong, Bi Huaqiang,

285
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:56,120
each of the three has their own use.

286
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,759
On the road ahead,

287
00:12:57,759 --> 00:12:59,639
we can look out for one another.

288
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,919
They're... they're all going?

289
00:13:03,559 --> 00:13:04,720
As the ancients said,

290
00:13:05,639 --> 00:13:06,960
too many cooks

291
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,919
spoil the broth, right?

292
00:13:09,519 --> 00:13:10,600
Idiot.

293
00:13:10,759 --> 00:13:12,240
Watch your mouth.

294
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:22,200
Who's here to cause trouble?

295
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,559
That remains to be seen.

296
00:13:25,559 --> 00:13:26,399
This... this...

297
00:13:26,399 --> 00:13:29,159
My wife, He Lingla,

298
00:13:29,399 --> 00:13:30,200
this time,

299
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,679
will also be coming along with us.

300
00:13:34,679 --> 00:13:35,399
Uncle Min,

301
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:37,600
the Jueda Ruins,

302
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,159
high altitude, freezing, low oxygen.

303
00:13:39,759 --> 00:13:41,440
Bringing just you is already pushing it.

304
00:13:42,519 --> 00:13:44,240
Dragging the whole family along isn't right.

305
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,279
Brother Chen,

306
00:13:46,279 --> 00:13:48,240
how is this "dragging the family along"?

307
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:50,519
These are my right-hand people.

308
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,440
Old Chen, I don't think this is a good idea.

309
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,879
Guys, let's go get hotpot.

310
00:13:55,879 --> 00:13:56,879
Let's go, let's go.

311
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:00,279
No,

312
00:14:00,519 --> 00:14:01,279
nobody leaves.

313
00:14:01,399 --> 00:14:03,240
We're showing plenty of sincerity,

314
00:14:03,559 --> 00:14:06,000
but they're not buying it.

315
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:11,000
This trip is going to be brutal.

316
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:13,519
My team has no room for dead weight.

317
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:15,399
Brother Chen,

318
00:14:15,399 --> 00:14:18,000
where's this "dead weight" talk coming from?

319
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:20,639
Don't forget, we have a signed contract.

320
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:24,879
We need to talk this through.

321
00:14:25,159 --> 00:14:26,440
Just as Advisor He said,

322
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,000
this little girl is just a gimmick.

323
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:30,519
My Godfather said,

324
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:34,320
we leave in fifteen minutes.

325
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,840
Wait, when do we leave?

326
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:37,320
You shouldn't startle people like that.

327
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,320
You scared me half to death.

328
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,399
Just... just ignore him.

329
00:14:39,399 --> 00:14:40,600
He's always startling people.

330
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,240
What's up, sis? Need something?

331
00:14:42,639 --> 00:14:44,480
Can I ride in your car?

332
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,279
Sure.

333
00:14:45,279 --> 00:14:47,080
What do you mean, sure?

334
00:14:47,759 --> 00:14:48,480
Sis,

335
00:14:48,879 --> 00:14:50,360
your Godfather treats you so well,

336
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,320
he dotes on you.

337
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,960
Wouldn't it be nice to ride with him?

338
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:55,240
The ride's too long, I'd be bored stiff.

339
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,039
Right, right, right.

340
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,799
The older folks should be together,

341
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,519
and us young people together.

342
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:00,759
Give me a break,

343
00:15:00,919 --> 00:15:03,039
we're the young ones here, okay?

344
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,639
You find them boring,

345
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:07,720
but I'm worried we'll be too rowdy for you.

346
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:09,559
Not rowdy, not rowdy at all.

347
00:15:09,559 --> 00:15:10,120
It'll be great.

348
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,519
Sis, ride in our car then.

349
00:15:11,519 --> 00:15:12,879
Front seat or back seat?

350
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,200
Come on, come on.

351
00:15:21,559 --> 00:15:22,279
Old Lian,

352
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:27,320
just let An Xiang ride with them.

353
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,559
They're young people,

354
00:15:29,559 --> 00:15:31,120
it's more fun together.

355
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:32,960
Take your medicine first.

356
00:15:34,159 --> 00:15:35,000
Give it to me.

357
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,480
Why is Commander Chen turning?

